# 🚀 Go Course API

A lightweight RESTful API built with **Go** for managing courses.
Implements full **CRUD operations** using an in-memory data store and HTTP JSON responses.

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

* Go (Golang)
* Gorilla Mux
* REST / JSON

---

## ⚙️ Getting Started

```bash
git clone https://github.com/AbhayMishra2722/GO.git
cd GO/24buildAPI
go mod tidy
go run main.go
```

Server runs on: **http://localhost:4000**

---

## 📡 API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint       | Description         |
| ------ | -------------- | ------------------- |
| GET    | `/`            | Health check        |
| GET    | `/courses`     | Get all courses     |
| GET    | `/course/{id}` | Get course by ID    |
| POST   | `/course`      | Create a new course |
| PUT    | `/course/{id}` | Update a course     |
| DELETE | `/course/{id}` | Delete a course     |

---

## 📦 Sample Request (Create)

```json
{
  "coursename": "Golang",
  "price": 299,
  "author": {
    "fullname": "Abhay",
    "website": "example.com"
  }
}
```

---

## 🧠 Notes

* Uses in-memory storage (no external database)
* Data resets on server restart
* Intended for learning and prototyping

---

